Business Overview

Duke Energy Corporation, together with its subsidiaries, operates as an energy company in the United States. It operates through three segments: Electric Utilities and Infrastructure, Gas Utilities and Infrastructure, and Commercial Renewables.

$DUK

$DUK is also currently more attractive then other utilities at the moment, not because of their 4.76% dividend yield, but because they are also trading at cheaper multiple compared to competitors such as $SO, $AEP, and $NEE.

(Cont)

At current valuations, I would say $DUK is a very appealing opportunity to consider adding to your portfolio, if you are looking for more current yield, or looking to diversify to the utilities sector.

(End)
